            <description>Lucy is a 3 year old mixed-breed dog that was presented to your clinic with a non-weight-bearing left hind limb lameness. You sedated Lucy with methadone (0.2 mg/kg) and dexmedetomidine (5 ug/kg) for radiographs. She was just gurneyed back to the ER after radiographs and you are reassessing her before placing her back into her cage. A team member reports that Lucy was stable throughout the procedure and last assessed her just before moving her back to the ER..</description>
